## What is Slope Exactly?

```
Slope = How steep the line is

m = Δy = rise (vertical change)
    Δx   run  (horizontal change)
```

---

## The Picture Explained

```
(x₁,y₁) •
          \  ↑ this distance
           \   = y₁ - y₂ (rise)
            \
             \ • (x₂,y₂)
←————————————→
this distance
= x₁ - x₂ (run)
```

---

## The Formula

```
m = y₁ - y₂
    ————————
    x₁ - x₂
```

---

## Why Two Versions?

The slide shows both are **equal:**

```
Version 1:      Version 2:
y₁ - y₂    =   y₂ - y₁
————————        ————————
x₁ - x₂        x₂ - x₁
```

Because:
```
y₁-y₂   -(y₂-y₁)   y₂-y₁
—————— = ————————— = ——————
x₁-x₂   -(x₂-x₁)   x₂-x₁
```

**Negatives cancel!** So order doesn't matter! ✅

---

## Simple Example 🚶

Two points: (1, 2) and (3, 6)

```
y↑
6|          •(3,6)
4|        /
2|    •(1,2)
0|____________→ x
  0   1   2   3

rise = 6-2 = 4
run  = 3-1 = 2

m = 4/2 = 2
```

For every 1 step right → 2 steps up!

---

## Connecting to Walking Example 🚶

```
Point 1 = (1hr, 2km)
Point 2 = (3hr, 6km)

m = 6-2 = 4 = 2 km/h
    3-1   2

Speed = slope! 🎯
```

---

## Key Rules to Remember

```
m > 0  → line goes UP ↗
m < 0  → line goes DOWN ↘
m = 0  → flat line →
m = ∞  → vertical line ↑
```

---

## In Calculus 🔮

```
Two points far apart:
m = y₂-y₁  (approximate slope)
    x₂-x₁

Bring points CLOSER and CLOSER:
m becomes MORE and MORE accurate

Points touch = EXACT slope
= DERIVATIVE! 🎯
```

This is **exactly** what calculus does! The formula you see here becomes the foundation of derivatives! 🤯

